org.apache.flink.api.java.functions

接口 KeySelector<IN,KEY>

  • 类型参数:
    IN - Type of objects to extract the key from.
    KEY - Type of key.
    所有超级接口:
    Function, Serializable

    @Public
public interface KeySelector<IN,KEY>
extends Function, Serializable
    The KeySelector allows to use arbitrary objects for operations such as reduce, reduceGroup, join, coGoup, etc. The extractor takes an object and returns the key for that object.

    • 方法概要

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      限定符和类型 方法和说明
      KEY getKey(IN value)
      User-defined function that extracts the key from an arbitrary object.

    • 方法详细资料

      • getKey

        KEY getKey(IN value)
    throws Exception
        User-defined function that extracts the key from an arbitrary object. For example for a class: 
                public class Word {
                String word;
                int count;
        }
        The key extractor could return the word as a key to group all Word objects by the String they contain. The code would look like this 
                public String getKey(Word w) {
                return w.word;
        }
        参数:
        value - The object to get the key from.
        返回:
        The extracted key.
        抛出:
        Exception - Throwing an exception will cause the execution of the respective task to fail, and trigger recovery or cancellation of the program.
